0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dab805f35a75674beaf0e5c8ed425c45730820da5cce4b853a0edbc128d55c816%26postID%3D68b86ae42129b4d6f58983a2%26postSlug%3Dxi-jinping-putin-hotmic-talking-about-living-to-150-longevity-2025-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs43587-025-00876-4%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elife%20extension%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20drawing%20billions%20in%20investment%20and%20becoming%20mainstream.%20Social%20media%20influencers%C2%A0who%20are%20attempting%C2%A0to%C2%A0reverse%C2%A0their%20biological%20age%20are%20selling%20lifestyle%20plans%20and%20food%20products%20to%20people%20who%20dream%20of%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20been%20engaging%20in%20antiaging%20research%20long%20before%20this%20trend%20boomed%2C%20studying%20ways%20to%20protect%20our%20cells%20from%20degradation.%20However%2C%20it's%20slow%20work%2C%20and%20no%20credible%20scientist%20has%20found%20a%20way%20to%20fight%20mortality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20David%20Sinclair%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20genetics%20at%20the%20Blavatnik%20Institute%20at%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%2C%20reported%20mouse%20experiments%20that%20suggested%20aging%20could%20be%20reversed%20by%20%26quot%3Breprogramming%26quot%3B%20certain%20cells.%20He%20extrapolated%20that%20the%20same%20may%20be%20true%20for%20humans%2C%20and%20that%20one%20day%20aging%20could%20be%20driven%20%26quot%3Bforwards%20and%20backwards%20at%20will.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20aging%20researchers%20agree%20that%20cellular%20reprogramming%20technology%20has%20some%20promise%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20evidence%20that%20it%20would%20work%20in%20humans.%20Even%20in%20mice%2C%20the%20researchers%20were%20not%20able%20to%20reverse%20their%20entire%20organism%20%26quot%3Bat%20will.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20Danish%20scientists%20published%20research%20suggesting%20that%20people%20whose%20gut