3E%20on%20how%20long%20humans%20can%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202024%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D890f5ff00b629ccc8fe7917544640c7cf1711609dd69e232df4f4be715deb701%26postID%3D68b86ae42129b4d6f58983a2%26postSlug%3Dxi-jinping-putin-hotmic-talking-about-living-to-150-longevity-2025-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs43587-024-00702-3%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20the%20dramatic%20life%20expectancy%20gains%20of%20the%20last%20century%20are%20flattening%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20research%2C%20from%201900%20to%202000%2C%20US%20life%20expectancy%20jumped%20from%2047%20to%2077%20years%2C%20thanks%20to%20breakthroughs%20like%20vaccines%2C%20antibiotics%2C%20sanitation%2C%20and%20better%20nutrition.%20But%20that%20rapid%20progress%20appears%20to%20be%20slowing%2C%20especially%20in%20wealthy%20countries%20where%20most%20people%20now%20survive%20well%20into%20old%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20somebody%20tells%20you%20that%20they%20know%20how%20to%20get%20you%20to%20100%2C%20don't%20listen%20to%20them%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20what%20they're%20talking%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20lead%20study%20author%20S.%20Jay%20Olshansky%2C%20a%20biostatistician%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%2C%20Chicago%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider's%20health%20correspondent%2C%20Hilary%20Brueck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20team%20estimated%20that%20in%20the%20best-case%20scenario%2C%20just%2015%25%20of%20women%20and%205%25%20of%20men%20alive%20today%20will%20reach%20age%20100.%20The%20finding%20is%20based%20on%2030%20years%20of%20demographic%20data%20from%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20richest%20nations%20with%20the%20most%20long-lived%20populations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20while%20that%20may%20dampen%20Xi%20and%20Putin's%20musings%2C%20Olshansky%20does%20offer%20a%20ray%20of%20hope%