s%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said%20of%20the%20first%20draft.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20arranged%20the%20story%20where%20it%20was%20a%20Matilda%20chapter%20and%20then%20a%20Vincent%20chapter%2C%20and%20then%20a%20Matilda%20chapter%20and%20then%20a%20Vincent%20chapter.%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20keep%20a%20certain%20pattern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20headshot%20of%20Rebecca%20Ross.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688a28a485e81483682eee99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERebecca%20Ross.%3Cp%3EPapillon%20Visuals%2FRebecca%20Ross%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wrote%20the%20entire%20book%2C%20the%20whole%20first%20draft%2C%20that%20way%2C%20and%20I%20just%20felt%20like%20something%20was%20missing%2C%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said%20of%20%26quot%3BWild%20Reverence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20she%20had%20already%20submitted%20the%20first%20draft%2C%20she%20got%20an%20idea.%20Ross%20asked%20her%20editor%20if%20she%20could%20rewrite%20the%20book%20from%20the%20first-person%20perspective%2C%20as%20she%20wanted%20to%20illustrate%20the%20differences%20between%20Matilda%20and%20Vincent%20as%20a%20goddess%20and%20a%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20does%20time%20feel%20like%20to%20her%2C%20versus%20Vincent%3F%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said%20about%20the%20types%20of%20differences%20she%20wanted%20to%20explore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20book's%20first%20line%20immediately%20came%20to%20her%20as%20she%20rewrote%20it.%20The%20god%20of%20war%20mentioned%20in%20the%20opening%20sentence%20didn't%20even%20exist%20in%20the%20novel%20before%20the%20change%2C%20but%20the%20first-person%20storytelling%20unlocked%20%26quot%3BWild%20Reverence%26quot%3B%20for%20Ross.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20shifted%20the%20book%20and%20rewrote%20the%20whole%20thing%2C%20I%20even%20changed%20where%20it%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20necessarily%20following%20the%20same%20structure.%20A%20very%20different%20type%20of%20story%20emerged.%20Even%20though%20the%20bones%20from%20the%20original%20were%20still%20there%2C%20it%20just%20felt%20very%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a14322c8-5a7d-43d8-9a2b-10f41c8308d2%5C%22%3EMeet%20Matilda%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWild%20Reverence%26quot%3B%20has%20five%20acts%2C%20which%20span%20decades%20and%20feature%20scenes%20in%20the%20worlds%20of%20the%20gods%20and%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20duration%20of%20Act%20One%2C%20Matilda%20and%20Vincent%20are%20children%2C%20which%20wasn't%20the%20case%20in%20Ross'%20first%20draft%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20it's%20so%20important%20because%20we%20see%20how%20she%20and%20Vincent%20are%20both%20developing%2C%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said%20of%20why%20she%20wanted%20to%20write%20about%20Matilda%20and%20Vincent%20as%20children.%20%26quot%3BThe%20things%20that%20impact%20them%2C%20who%20they%20become%20when%20they%20reunite%20many%20years%20later%2C%20we%20see%20who%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%26quot%3BWild%20Reverence%26quot%3B%20by%20Rebecca%20Ross.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6887d59ff748d8c055f66711%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223030%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BWild%20Reverence%26quot%3B%20by%20Rebecca%20Ross.%3Cp%3ESaturday%20Books%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWild%20Reverence%26quot%3B%20develops%20differently%20from%20%26quot%3BDivine%20Rivals%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20readers%20shouldn't%20expect%20a%20continuation%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BLetters%20of%20Enchantment%26quot%3B%20series.%20It's%20also%20an%20adult%20novel%20instead%20of%20a%20young-adult%20book%2C%20so%20the%20tone%20is%20distinct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20has%20the%20emotional%