%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFor%20many%2C%20the%20mother%20also%20ends%20up%20showing%20the%20way.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20Aadi%20had%20been%20neurotypical%2C%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20bothered%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20things%2C%20including%20my%20own%20therapy.%20Because%20I%20was%20pushed%20to%20a%20corner%2C%20because%20things%20got%20dark%2C%20I%20had%20to.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20thankful%20now%20because%20it%20has%20made%20me%20a%20better%20parent%2C%20and%20a%20more%20aware%2C%20better%20person%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Swaati.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru-based%20play%20therapist%20and%20parenting%20coach%20Manju%20decided%20to%20homeschool%20her%20daughter%2C%20Lavanya%2C%20after%20her%20diagnosis.%20Since%20then%2C%20she%20has%20worked%20to%20support%20the%20community%2C%20designing%20customised%20activities%20and%20therapies%20based%20on%20close%20interaction%20with%20children%20and%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriya%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F371845%2Fadhd-at-workplace-employee-journey-with-adhd-in-his-career-tips-to-manage-inattention-distraction-symptoms%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enormalises%20her%20son%E2%80%99s%20ADHD%20both%20at%20home%20and%20in%20society%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20very%20open%20with%20Arhant%20and%20everybody%20else%20about%20his%20ADHD%2C%20right%20from%20the%20beginning.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20empowering.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20very%20clear%20with%20him%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20some%20free%20pass%20we%20use%20to%20get%20away%20with%20anything.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20touch%20of%20humour%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20not%20something%20to%20give%20up%20on%20%E2%80%94%20like%20oh%20I%20have%20diabetes%2C%20so%20I%20might%20as%20well%20eat%20%3Cem%3Egulab%20jamuns%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20die%E2%80%A6It%E2%80%99s%20something%20we%20deal%20with%20and%20manage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelja%20recalls%20being%20a%20young%20mother%20facing%20the%20dreaded%20PTMs%20that%20every%20parent%20of%20a%20neurodivergent%20child%20identifies%20with.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20kept%20telling%20me%20how%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20everything%20wrong.%20I%20asked%20them%20to%20pause%20and%20tell%20me%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20right%2C%20because%20I%20refuse%20to%20accept%20otherwise.%20We%20have%20to%20be%20very%20strong%20advocates%20for%20our%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDoing%20away%20with%20labels%20and%20embracing%20some%20PQ!%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelja%20says%20her%20personal%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20both%20as%20a%20partner%20to%20her%20husband%2C%20Children%20First%20co-founder%20Dr%20Amit%20Sen%2C%20and%20as%20mother%20to%20a%20son%20with%20ADHD%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20her%20have%20%E2%80%9Can%20easy%20relationship%20with%20the%20diagnosis%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnita%20is%20blunt%20about%20it.%20%E2%80%9CLabels%20are%20not%20so%20great%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20us%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20important%20to%20an%20extent%20because%20we%20work%20with%20children%20and%20some%20broad%20directives%20are%20helpful.%20But%20each%20child%20is%20different%2C%20and%20too%20much%20of%20the%20specifics%20are%20not%20useful.%20In%20the%20day-to-day%20of%20life%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20not%20much%20need%20for%20such%20language.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Swaati%2C%20the%20paperwork%20was%20just%20a%20means%20to%20access%20accommodations.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20reading%20and%20my%20interactions%20with%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20people%20helped%20me%20make%20my%20peace%20with%20how%20autism%20is%20an%20umbrella%20ter